name: SolidOrganTransplantProcedureCodes
title: Solid Organ Transplant Procedure Codes
description: This value set has not been tested in a clinical environment. Please use with caution.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Solid organ transplant procedures, along with diagnostic procedures performed on transplanted solid organs.),(Data Element Scope: Includes ICD10-PCS codes that represent heart, lung, kidney, pancreas, and liver transplants, as well as combined organ transplants of these organs, and procedures performed on the solid organs post-transplant. The purpose of this value set is to identify evidence that an individual underwent a solid organ transplant procedure in the past.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes ICD10-PCS codes that represent heart, lung, kidney, pancreas, land liver transplants, as well as combined organ transplants of these organs, and procedures done to the solid organ post-transplant.),(Exclusion Criteria: Other types of transplants not listed in the inclusion criteria, tissue transplants.)
